How can I contact Dotdigital?
You are entering into a contract with Dotdigital
Purpose and legal basis for Processing
When you negotiate with us to buy a product or start using one of our services, we process some personal information so that we can enter into an agreement with you or the organisation that you represent.
The legal basis we rely on to process your personal data is article 6(1)(b) of the GDPR, which allows us to process personal data when this is necessary for the performance of a contract to which you are a party or in order for us to take steps at your request prior to entering into a contract.
What we need
If you are entering into a contract with us, we will need your full contact details including address, email and telephone number as well as your job title or position in your business. If we need further information, this will be made clear to you as we will ask you for it at the time.
What we do with it
We store customer contracts and related personal information within our internal CRM system, and our legal case management system is shared with internal employees on a need-to-know basis via email and Dropbox.
What are your rights
As we are processing your personal data for the purpose of entering into a contract with you, you have the right in principle to data portability. However, there are limitation as to when this right applies.
You subscribe to our content
What type of content can you subscribe to
You can subscribe to read blogs, case studies, events and webinars, product demonstrations, product updates and videos.
Purpose and legal basis for processing
Our purpose for collection this information is so that we can send you the requested content, and our legal basis is your consent which you have indicated by providing us with your details. We may also send you details of other products or services that we think you will be interested in and our legal basis for this is where we believe that you have a legitimate interest and in line with your preferences. Set your Dotdigital email communications preferences
What we need
If you wish to receive information from us, you will be asked to provide your contact information including your name, your organisation’s name and other details about your organisation.
What we do with it
Your details will be held on our CRM and marketing platform databases and the information you have requested will be sent to you. We may also send you details of other products or services.
What are your rights?
We rely on your consent to process the personal data you give us. This means you have the right to withdraw your consent at any time. As we also rely on legitimate interest, you do have the right to object. If you do that, we’ll update our records immediately to reflect your wishes. Please also see summary of your data protection rights above.
You are representing your organisation
We hold the names and contact details of individuals acting in their capacity as representatives of their organisations, across the business. The legal basis is article 6(1)(c) of the GDPR for any legal obligation or article 6(1)(f) because the processing is within our legitimate interests as a business.
Visitors to our website
What we need
When you visit our company websites, we collect internet log information and details of visitor behaviour patterns. We do this to find out things such as the number of visitors to various parts of the site.
Cookies
We use cookies, which are small files with a code that is stored on your device, with your consent. They are retrieved from your device when you next visit the site. This allows the site to recognise information about your use and browsing.
We use a cookie consent tool on our website which notifies you of our use of cookies when you first enter our site of cookies when you first enter our site and gives you the opportunity to refuse the use of cookies or to consent by accepting use of cookies on our site.
Full information on which cookies we use is available in our Cookies Policy, along with guidance about how you can set your browser to refuse all or some cookies (please note that your decisions may affect some use of the site).
When you make an enquiry or contact our support team
Purpose and legal basis for processing
When you contact Dotdigital via phone, email or live chat to make an enquiry, we collect information, including your personal data, so that we can assist with your enquiry.
Where you have no prior business relationship with Dotdigital the legal basis we rely on to process your personal data is article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR , which allows us to process personal data when this is necessary for our legitimate interests. Where there is a business relationship the legal basis we rely on is article 6 (1) (b) of the GDPR, which allows us to process personal data when this is necessary for the performance of a contract to which you are a party.
What we need
We need enough information from you to answer your enquiry. This information may be obtained for training purposes, or to establish the facts of transactions and enquiries as well as to ensure compliance with our policies and procedures and any regulations we are subject to.
What we do with it
We’ll keep a record of your enquiry on Zendesk & intercom, our support ticketing system We use the information supplied to us to deal with the enquiry and any subsequent issues that may arise, and to check on the level of service we provide.
What are your rights?
Where we are processing your personal data for the purpose of entering into a contract with you, you have the right in principle to data portability. However, there are limitation as to when this right applies. Where we are processing your personal data for our legitimate interests, you have the right to object to our processing of your personal data. There are legitimate reasons why we may refuse your objection, which depend on why we are processing it.
You wish to attend, or have attended, an event
Purpose and legal basis for processing
Our purpose for collecting this information is so we can facilitate the event and provide you with an acceptable service.
The legal basis we rely on for processing your personal data is your consent under article 6(1)(a) of the GDPR. When we collect any information about dietary or access requirements, we also need your consent (under article 9(2)(a)) as this type of information is classed as special category data.
What we need
If you wish to attend one of our events, you will be asked to provide your contact information including your organisation’s name and, if offered a place, information about any dietary requirements or access provisions you may need.
What are your rights
We rely on your consent to process the personal data you give us to facilitate the event. This means you have the right to withdraw your consent at any time. If you do that, we’ll update our records immediately to reflect your wishes.
Integrations & Connectors
Purpose and legal basis for processing
Dotdigital uses several suppliers of integration platforms for clients wanting to link their Dotdigitial account to supported third party e-commerce systems. The legal basis we rely on for processing your personal data is your consent under article 6(1)(a) of the GDPR.
Please note: when connecting Dotdigital SaaS applications to your Google workspace account using OAuth, we confirm Google Workspace APIs and the data passed within are not used to develop, improve, or train generalized/non-personalized AI and/or ML models.
What are your rights
We rely on your consent to process the personal data you give us to facilitate the event. This means you have the right to withdraw your consent at any time by cancelling the integration link.
